Residents of Zimmerman in Nairobi county are calling on the National Construction Authority [NCA] to come to their aid, after a private developer allegedly constructed a house without proper safety measures’ in place. According to the residents the house had been earmarked for demolition, however the construction has continued with several accidents having been reported including damage caused to vehicles parked nearby. The residents are now calling on relevant authorities to come to their aid, failure to which they will take the law in their own hands. 